4:
Oh, T-Telluna! Your power... Those
sparks! I-if I can just...
13: Ah! It's you again! Hello there!
16: Eep! I-I need to go! I'm sorry!
32:
I just noticed him hanging around
me for the last few hours.
36:
I figured he must have some reason
for following me, but whenever I call
out to him, he runs away.
46:
And concerning. Perhaps it would be
best to tell the Guild about this.
51:
N-no! You shouldn't judge a book by
its cover!
56: Yeah, in this case, we kinda should...
61:
Better safe than sorry. For now, we
shall escort you home.
70:
Of course! Ah, and we'll take some of
those bags. They look pretty heavy.
75:
Wow, thanks a lot! Ehehe, you're
right, they ARE heavy!
82:
Grannie, I brought the stuff you
asked for!
85:
Welcome back, Telluna. Thank you
for always helping me.
89:
You don't need to thank me. That's
what neighbors are for, silly!
95: Ah! M-my back! Ow, ow, ow...
103:
U-um... Could you guys help Grannie
over to her chair?
113:
Phew... Thank you. I should be fine
now.
116:
I'm glad you guys were here to help.
I can't touch anybody right now...
120:
Ah, right. Um... This'll sting a bit, so
sorry in advance.
129:
For some reason, my body collects
and stores elemental thunder inside
me... I can kinda control it, but...
133:
If I don't discharge it before touching
someone, it can really hurt them...
138: I see... That's quite the predicament...
141:
So this is your first time hearing
about her powers. I thought you
were friends of hers, but that doesn't
seem to be the case...
143:
Who are you people, and what
business do you have with Telluna?
150:
I just met Alk and the others while
shopping today!
155:
They were worried about me going
home by myself, so they offered to
come with me. Don't worry, Grannie,
they're super nice people!
158:
Ah... Is that so? My apologies. I
shouldn't have accused you without
any proof...
160:
Telluna is a very sweet child... But
she's as gullible as she is kind.
163:
Jeez, Grannie, you worry too much!
I'm not THAT easy to trick.
166:
Oh? I seem to remember you giving
all your money to a con artist
recently...
170:
Urgh... B-but he said he was in
trouble...
173:
Telluna, take this. It's not much, but
think of it as a tip for the errands you
ran today.
177: Y-you don't need to pay me!
180:
Of course I do! You haven't been
paying your rent, have you? At this
rate, you're going to be evicted!
184:
Th-that's okay! I might be small, but
I'm sturdy! I don't mind sleeping
outside!
188: N-no, that's a little too far...
193:
Telluna, would you like to stay with
us?
197:
Ah, we do have an open room. There
are a few conditions for living there,
though...
202:
A-are you sure I wouldn't be a
burden?
207:
Of course not. But we won't force
you to go either.
210:
...Telluna, this must be fate. You
should go with them.
213:
Okay! I promise I'll be a good little
houseguest!
222:
Thank you! And I'll do everything I
can to pay you guys back!
226:
If you need help with anything, just
leave it to me!
